        <div id="q1">
        <h4 >What is this thing and why is it here?</h4>

        <p>This app is an interface for the Deep End community radio, an online radio station created for the members of the Deep End / Venus Theory Discord server to showcase and present their work.</p> 

        <p>There's a lot of cool and varied music being made by everyone in the server, and this gives us an opportunity to hear what everyone is up to, appreciate some good music, get feedback on what we're doing, and to provide an outlet in to the world when there's so much competition for playtime on other platforms. It was made for the community to get involved with and a platform to encourage constructive conversations.</p>
        </div>

        <br />



        <h4 id="q2">Do I have to create an account?</h4>

        <p>No, if you don't want an account you don't have to have one, you can listen to the stream as a guest user without problems. Or you use one the raw streams listed further down the page with a different player.</p>

        <p>If you do create an account, it might also help with new features as they get developed in the future, things like notifications if someone likes your song, or a intelligent submission form that remembers details etc, but none of that works yet so it's entirely up to you.</p>


        <br />


        <h4 id="q3">Do I need an account to submit a track?</h4>

        <p>If you want to submit a track through the app, then you will need an account, this is to stop spammers and unsolicted uploads.</p>

        <p>I absolutely understand some people will not want to make another account for a number of perfectly legitimate reasons, if that's you that's fine, just hit me up in the Discord (@@smadger) and let me know, I'll let you know what I need and you can DM me the track.</p>

        <br />


        <h4 id="q4">Why do you want my email?</h4>

        <p>If you forget your password, you should be able to reset your accont yourself without having to wait for someone to reply to you, and I don't want to know your password, it has nothing to do with me unless something has gone massively wrong. This way you can use your email to recover your account, whenever you need, and I don't have to be involved. You can use any email you want, as long as you can get the activation code from it when you set the account up in the first place.</p>


        <br />

        <h4 id="q5">Do I need a new account for each artist name I use?</h4>

        <p>No, just complete the form with a different artist name. The form should give you suggestions for previous artist names you've sued. If you get stuck just send me a DM in Discord (@@smadger) and I'll sort things out.</p>

        <br />


        <h4 id="q6">What if you've alrady uploaded a track for the radio?</h4>

        <p>It's the same situation as above, if you don't want an account that's fine. But if you create an account let me know and I'll get things linked in the background.</p>

        <br />



